  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This assessment evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors are formally assessed; six are flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved required gradation levels under the Minimal profile submission. Intended use scope: pre-market submission support for a Class III implantable rotary blood pump operating at 3–6 L/min and 3000–6000 RPM, targeting prediction of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within ±15% of in-vitro measurements. Decision: Accepted under Minimal profile.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-cou2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-nih-prediction-class3-vad",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
